===Etymology===
Phonetic variant of {{term|seely}}.
From {{etyl|ang|en}} *{{term||sǣliġ}}, "blessed", (attested only in form {{term|gesælig|ġesǣliġ}}), from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{term/t|gem-pro|*sēlīgaz}}.  Cognate with West Frisian {{term|sillich|lang=fy}}, Dutch {{term|zalig|lang=nl}}, German {{term|selig|lang=de}}. More at {{l|en|sely}}.

